				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Adventure stone upgrade????<a name="11774"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Nov 4 03 12:22 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>you can buy charms from LDoN merchants that only work in LDoN but you can put the stone into them.  If you want to later change you can buy the solvent and disolve it.  Then just hail the wayfarer in any camp to get new one.  The stats should still be there.  You also need to zone to see the change in stats after your 10th win and you hail the guy to get the messages.  If you have not hailed the guy after every 2 victorys just keep hailing until you get the red you need to do more adventures message.  There is also the, as mentioned, free charm available in PoK from the dwarf in the building between the PoT stone and the soulbinder.  Hail all the dwarves in that building till find the right one.  Think he is only one but could be wrong.  The solvents are of 3 types.  You need to by the one for whatever slot you are wanting disolved.  For instance you have a pre LDoN wep with 1 slot then you need to by the type/slot 1 solvent.  If you have an item with 2 slots and want to disolve the aug in the second slot you need to get the type/slot 2 solvent.  The solvents are sold at the magus in each camp.</span></td>
