			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Adventure stone upgrade????<a name="17668"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 28 04 3:47 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Sin, the advantage to Guk is that it only takes 3 or 4 times to learn how to pull it (looking for hidden mobs in trenches or walls, using bind sight/lull and once you do, it's relatively easy because the groups wanting to do Guk tend to be fairly well-equipped and AA'd.  Marginal groups do not want to hit Guk.
<br />

<br />
That said, one tends to get hit a lot pulling Guk.  Being able to take a few punches thrown at you while getting off the mezz song can make all the difference in the world.  Thus, upgrading AC and HP while investing in defensive AAs will have an immediate impact.
<br />

<br />
As for EC, the abundance of runners adding almost forces CC to not melee.  DPS here is very important and if your group doesn't have a rogue/ranger for DPS, then a way to debuff resistances becomes important.
<br />

<br />
Intercepting the adds in EC is really more important than adding directly to the group's DPS.   Intersections are particularly vulnerable places.
<br />

<br />
Also,it is much easier to pull EC if the arrival of mobs into camp is  staggered, such as pulling with Largo's or using a mezz/pull technique.  Throwing a ranger in front of them also works to slow them down, a little.<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
As for that pesky Adventurer's stone, later on it adds +3 to HP/Mana per 10 wins in a theme.  The increase to all stats tracks the HP total (e.g., +42 HP means +4 to all stats; +51 HP means +5 to all stats).  It starts going faster.
<br />

<br />

<br />
</span></td>
